replies.bodyText: Can I have a bit more detail please. I can't quite figure what you mean.
replies.author: jonbaber

replies.bodyText: You could make a BclToolsBuilder interface, with an @immutable annotation, and all the construction methods as interface methods. Then let Immutables generate all the internal state of the builder, etc. Only awkward bit is you'd probable need to create a special build method or something to return an actual command... not that fussed about it, just if you think its a good idea.
replies.author: pauldwolfe

timeline.bodyText: FYI i guess you've figured it out, but this will give you the default VM of 32 CPU and 120GB RAM. You can use VirtualMachinePerformanceProfile.custom() to tune that
